          "End of Program Graduation",
          "Complete Graduation (1) vs Not Complete (0)",
          "38842 students",
          "All courses at University of Toronto",
          "Academic History",
          "[StudentID, Number of Credits attempted- Divided by Department and average grade across Department ]",
          "End of First Year",
          "Each dataset has 142 features since there are 71 Departments at University of Toronto.\n\nTarget variable is computed according to the rule: Registered for 5 credits, did not succeed in at least 18 and did not take a course in 3 semesters were defined as dropouts. \n\nAuthors also perform a feature importance analysis via Permutation Descrease Importance.\n\nPermutation is preferred since it does not show to be a reliable indicator of variable importance in different types of predictors. \n\n",
          "CART\nRandom Forest\nLogistic Regression",
          "Holdout Method",
          "{Accuracy: 0.7884 - Random Forest #3, Precision: 0.5295 - Random Forest #3, Recall: 0.7500 - Random Forest #3}",
          "Authors use the term class-specific Accuracy, which by the text seems to be precision.\n\nAuthors fiund RF to be the best model even though they attempt 3 forms of RF. ",
          "Use of Grades to predict success. \n\nDoes not consider option of a student being in multiple majors or specializations. \n\nInneficient addressing of Nans.\n\nHoldout method is split in 90%-5%-5%, which is unorthodox. "
        ]
      ],
      "index": 4
    }
