    {
      "id": "1904750c-f3ba-8036-8840-e8c21b303d6e",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The authors take 10 years worth of data from a Chinese university and create 2 Random Forest models. The first model is meant to predict end-of-program success just from using data from the first 2 semesters. The second RF is used for interpretation purposes as it is used to understand in which courses the successful students first registered. ",
      "raw": {
        "object": "block",
